text: Victory is a town in Essex County, Vermont, United States. The population of the town was 70 in the 2020 census. ==Geography== According to the United States Census Bureau, the town is 43.0 square miles in area (111.4 km2). 43.0 square miles (111.3 km2) is made up of land. 0.04 square miles (0.1 km2) (0.07%) is made up of water. ==References== ==Other websites== * Town of Victory Category:Towns in Vermont
title: Victory, Vermont
